  "text": "Assignment of the NMR Spectra of ISCU(M108I) and ISCU(D39V). Because ISCU(M108I) was found to be fully structured, we decided to compare its properties with those of another ISCU variant, ISCU(D39V), known to be structured. [CITATION_1] By collecting and analyzing a series of 2D and 3D NMR spectra of protein samples labeled uniformly with Figure 4A ). Many of the residues exhibiting chemical shift differences in the two variants map to the ISCU− NFS1 interface in the structure of the complex [CITATION_2] ( Figure 4B ). The 58 FKTFGCGSAI 67 region includes a cysteine residue that ligates the cluster. As expected, most other perturbations map to residues near the sequence differences (residues 39 and 108).",
